lding a biohybrid brain interface that grows living neurons on silicon to restore sensory functions like sight—but eventually to explore new parts of the brain and new senses.", "And we don’t care as much about what they’re building exactly as we do about what they’re learning about how they’re building."], "source_family_ids": ["naval_frontier_founders_industrial_2026", "naval_sell_truth_2026"], "speaker": "Nivi", "speaker_status": "source_provided", "themes": ["persuasion_and_sales", "time_compute_substitution", "token_economics", "truth_and_credibility", "startup_organization", "hardware_engineering", "vertical_integration", "software_production", "future_of_work", "ai_capability_and_agi", "ai_coding_agents", "manufacturing", "geopolitics", "institutional_change"]}
